              "coded_information": [
                "IOCH"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                "  Ionization chamber filled with isobutane gas at",
                "   a pressure of 43 mb, allowing the identification of",
                "   A/q. The chamber consists of two regions of gas,",
                "   delta-E1 = 9 cm and delta-E2 = 6 cm, separated by",
                "   a grid - for fission fragments"
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "COIN",
                "GE",
                "GE"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                "  The gamma-rays deexciting the isomeric",
                " states were detected by a Clover Ge detector  and",
                " three single Ge crystals of the Miniball array",
                " assembled in the same cryostat. These detectors were",
                " placed perpendicular to the ion beam in a close",
                " geometry, possible as the ionization chamber was 6 cm",
                " thick. The total efficiency for gamma-ray detection",
                " was 20% and 4% for photons of 100 keV and 1MeV,",
                " respectively."
              ]
            }
